</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="negative">The</a> @HI{{nai}} form before @HI{{@EM{{tsumori}}}} indicates the speaker's intention of not doing something.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ashitakarahatabakowo@KJ{{suck}}wanai@EM{{tsumori}}desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'm determined not to smoke from tomorrow.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
A negative intention may also be expressed by using @HI{{@EM{{tsumori}}hanai}}.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{attend^matter}}ga@KJ{{busy}}shiinode,@FG{{@KJ{{now^night}}:kon'ya}}no@KT{{pa-texi-}}ni@EM{{tsumori}}hanai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I'm busy with work today so I'm not thinking of going to the party tonight.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="past">@HI{{@EM{{tsumoridatta}}}}</a> indicates that speaker intended to do something, but it never happened.

<table class="sentence">
