  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I intended to phone you, but I forgot. I'm sorry.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
This form may also be used with a negative verb to indicate that one had intended <em>not</em> to do something, but ended up doing it.

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KT{{pa-texi-}}niha@KJ{{going}}kanai@EM{{tsumorideshita}}ga,omoshirosounanode@KJ{{going}}kukotonishita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I had intended not to go to the party, but it looked like it would be fun, so I decided to go after all.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

